thread.title: Rachel Maddow Gets Mocked On Twitter Following Her Trump Tax Return Special
thread.title_full: Rachel Maddow Gets Mocked On Twitter Following Her Trump Tax Return Special

author: Jorge Alonso
title: Rachel Maddow Gets Mocked On Twitter Following Her Trump Tax Return Special
text:
Earlier tonight, MSNBC’s Rachel Maddow peaked the country’s interest by teasing that she had President Donald Trump’s tax return from 2005. 
BREAKING: We've got Trump tax returns. Tonight, 9pm ET. MSNBC.
(Seriously).
— Rachel Maddow MSNBC (@maddow) March 14, 2017 
What we've got is from 2005… the President's 1040 form… details to come tonight 9PM ET, MSNBC.
— Rachel Maddow MSNBC (@maddow) March 15, 2017 

Maddow then went on a 20 minute monologue explaining why Trump’s business ties with a Russian oligarch is the reason why the President should be forthcoming with his tax returns. 
Maddow’s revelations ended up being severely underwhelming and she was mercilessly mocked on the Twittersphere for it. 
Rachel Maddow hyped this tax return up like Funk Flex did for Meek Mills non-existent Drake diss
— Young Kaylatouille (@KaylaPatra) March 15, 2017 
Rachel Maddow is now the Funk Flex of journalism.
— Universally Arcanaic (@galaxytidesx) March 15, 2017 


President Trump to Rachel Maddow: "I paid $38 million in Federal income taxes in 2005. Cash me outside, how bowdah?" pic.twitter.com/HJxq2wr8Al 
— CJ NapIes (@cjnapIes) March 15, 2017 
It takes less time to fill out your taxes than for Rachael Maddow to get to what's in Trump's taxes
— Eric Stangel (@EricStangel) March 15, 2017 


Trump bought a house for 40 million and a Russian oligarch paid him more than double for the same 4 years later?
— Mni Wiconi (@MuditaJason) March 15, 2017 
The last time I saw an expose like this one from Rachel @maddow it involved Geraldo Rivera, Capone's vault and an empty soda bottle.
— Steven Getman (@stevengetman) March 15, 2017 
Rachel Maddow right now. #TRUMPSTAXES #msnbc #trumpstaxreturns #trump pic.twitter.com/jnRDO2CRw2 
— Kenneth Yovano (@YeahKenny) March 15, 2017 


Rachel Maddow's next big TV spectacular will be Donald Trumps 1997 dental records. #TrumpTaxReturn 
— MARK SIMONE (@MarkSimoneNY) March 15, 2017 
Could you imagine if Rachel Maddow wrote the "Star Wars" opening crawls?
— Frank Pallotta (@frankpallotta) March 15, 2017 
I just filed my 2016 taxes in the time it has taken @maddow to get to the point about Trump's 2005 return.
— David Martosko (@dmartosko) March 15, 2017 


Livestream of #Maddow revealing Trump's taxes pic.twitter.com/rSgzslpeNB 
— Daniel José Older (@djolder) March 15, 2017 
Rachel Maddow on Trump's 2005 Tax Return. pic.twitter.com/13DZmnG9ZJ 
— Dylan (@DylansFreshTake) March 15, 2017 


Rachel Maddow and MSNBC pic.twitter.com/AaLVfZUSYv 
— Around The League™ (@RTSportsTalk) March 15, 2017 
Rachel Maddow is why Trump wins in 2020
— AGGs (@gourlax) March 15, 2017 

Gotta come harder than that Rachel Maddow.
